# Phishing Attack Practical using manual method, Apache, Ravana, and Zphisher on Kali Linux or Ubuntu.

## ‚úÖ **Practical Overview**

**Goal:**

- Host a fake login page locally using Apache.
- Use **Ravana** or **Zphisher** to automate phishing.
- Generate a **short URL** to disguise the phishing link.

---

## üîπ **Step 1: Manual Phishing Page Using Apache**

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Open **Apache‚Äôs HTML directory**

```bash
cd /var/www/html
pwd  # Should output: /var/www/html
```

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Remove existing `index.html`

```bash
sudo rm index.html
```

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Create your **fake page**

- Inspect Facebook‚Äôs login page ‚Üí Copy the **HTML source code**.
- Paste into a new `index.html`:

```bash
sudo nano index.html
```

- Paste code ‚Üí Save with **Ctrl + O**, **Enter**, then exit with **Ctrl + X**.

---

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Restart **Apache2**

```bash
sudo systemctl restart apache2.service
```

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Test it

Open **browser** ‚Üí

- `http://localhost` **OR** `http://127.0.0.1` **OR** your local IP.
- You should see the fake Facebook login.

---

## üîπ **Loopback (127.0.0.1)**

**Note:**
`127.0.0.1` is the **loopback address** ‚Üí The machine talks to itself.
**Phrase:** _‚ÄúThere‚Äôs no place like 127.0.0.1.‚Äù_

---

## üîπ **Step 2: Phishing with Ravana**

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Download **Ravana**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/princekrvert/Ravana.git
cd Ravana
ls
```

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Run Ravana

```bash
chmod +x ravana.sh
./ravana.sh
```

- Choose option **2** ‚Üí Instagram phishing.
- Start **localhost** ‚Üí Option **1** ‚Üí Random port.
- Example: `http://127.0.0.1:8874`

Victim enters:

```
Username: john
Password: john@123
```

Captured in Ravana‚Äôs **logs**.

---

## üîπ **Step 3: Phishing with Zphisher**

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Download **Zphisher**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/htr-tech/zphisher.git
cd zphisher
ls
```

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Run Zphisher

```bash
chmod +x zphisher.sh
./zphisher.sh
```

- Choose your target (Facebook, Instagram, etc.).
- Zphisher sets up the phishing page.
- It gives you **localhost** and sometimes **cloud link**.

---

## üîπ **Step 4: Shorten the URL**

To make the phishing link less suspicious:

- Copy the localhost or forwarding URL.
- Go to:

  - [https://www.shorturl.at/](https://www.shorturl.at/)
  - [https://bitly.com/](https://bitly.com/)

- Paste link ‚Üí Get short version.
- Share the **short URL**.

---

## ‚úÖ **Important Notes**

| **Command/Tool**            | **Use**                             |
| --------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| `cd /var/www/html`          | Apache web root.                    |
| `rm index.html`             | Remove default page.                |
| `nano index.html`           | Create fake page.                   |
| `systemctl restart apache2` | Restart Apache.                     |
| **Ravana**                  | Automated phishing toolkit.         |
| **Zphisher**                | Automated phishing toolkit.         |
| `127.0.0.1`                 | Loopback address for local testing. |
| `shorturl.at` / `bitly.com` | Mask phishing URLs.                 |

